  "learningObjective": "Read a thermometer in degrees Celsius",
  "coreIdea": "A thermometer measures temperature in degrees Celsius.",
  "examples": [
    "25°C is a warm day. The liquid in the thermometer rises to 25. 🌡️",
    "0°C is freezing. The liquid in the thermometer is at the bottom. 🌡️",
    "40°C is a hot day. The liquid in the thermometer rises to 40. 🌡️"
  ],
  "misconceptions": [
    "Students may think the thermometer measures length instead of temperature.",
    "Students may read the scale backwards, thinking higher is colder.",
    "Students may confuse the unit °C with other measurement units."
  ],
